{
  "stem": "18102.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 425.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The, the stories did filter down to me because you couldn't help but overhear various stories.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Eventually my mother decided that we should move back to our own house because she was afraid that standing empty as it was, it was a [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] target of looting perhaps and that it was best that we occupied the premises.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we moved back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Bombing had, after all, stopped, and there was no reason to remain in my father's building.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we moved back, and within a day after our moving back, German soldiers arrived to look for my father just as they had expected would happen.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They wanted him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They wanted to arrest him as a hostage.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They came and searched the premises, poked in the closets and the drawers, talked very loud in a language I recognized was-- had many similarities to Yiddish, which of course I knew.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was in a harsh tongue, and I didn't fully understand what it is they were saying.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother responded.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the fear and the tears welling in her eyes transmitted to me and my grandmother with us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was the personal-- that brought the war very much personally to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was the first time that the soldiers were that close to me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In fact, my memory is that one of them tapped me on the head.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I could only-- you know, I didn't-- I never looked really up at them, but I, I looked at their boots.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was their boots that left the memory and the imprint on me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Well, my father wasn't there so they couldn't get him, and they left eventually.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it was the first real turning point which proved the, the difference between life and death perhaps in our lives.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
